<seg id=1> Schools in Zhejiang closed near site of natural disaster resume classes. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Hangzhou, September 2nd, by Haixiong Shen, Xiquan Sheng- Number 17 Typhoon caused terrible damage to the Zhejian's school systems, schools are closed near to the site of the natural disaster.  School buildings and equipment were destroyed in 1500 schools. </seg>
<seg id=3> After a great deal of effort by both the local Government and Residents to repair damage from the storm, most schools are now reopening. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Zhejiang Department of Education sent out workers in teams to Wenzhou and  Taizhou, etc. to supervise cleanup and recovery work. </seg>
<seg id=5> More than twenty cadres from Wenzhou's Educational Community were divided into seven teams and sent to Leqing, Xinhai, Dongtong, Pinyang,etc. to help repair the schools and prepare for the new school year to begin.  This Educational Committee also spent 200,000 Yaun on disaster relief. </seg>
<seg id=6> All the Educational Departments in the cities and counties in the disaster area gave free or reduced tuition to those students whose families were in financial difficulties because of the disaster to insure that students will be able to return to school on time. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> All the school leaders and teachers of schools in the disaster areas volunteered to go back to work early, carefully cleaning up the school environment to insure a clean and sterile environment for students and to repair the damaged buildings. </seg>
<seg id=8> Wenzhou Education Committee and the Youth League of Wenzhou City Community joined the teachers and students in those disaster areas, in starting activities for the public to "show love and support to these schools".  Up till now, this city has already raised more than 1,000,000 yuan from all different sources. </seg>
</p>
